Property Documentation

◆ ClientRsaPrivateKey

RsaPrivateKey^ IonicSecurity::SDK::CreateDeviceRequest::ClientRsaPrivateKey
getset

The RSA private key to be used by the client for decryption and signature verifiation.

Parameters
[in]mPrivateKeyThe RSA private key.

The client RSA key pair is optional. If it is not provided, then the key pair will be generated during the call to Agent::CreateDevice().

If only one piece of the key pair is provided, then Agent::CreateDevice() will throw an SdkException.

◆ ClientRsaPrivateKeyBase64

String^ IonicSecurity::SDK::CreateDeviceRequest::ClientRsaPrivateKeyBase64
set

The Base64 encoded RSA private key to be used by the client for decryption and signature verifiation.

Parameters
[in]msRsaPrivateKeyBase64The Base64 encoded RSA private key.

The client RSA key pair is optional. If it is not provided, then the key pair will be generated during the call to Agent::CreateDevice().

If only one piece of the key pair is provided, then Agent::CreateDevice() will throw an SdkException.

If the Base64 encoded RSA private key fails to load, an SdkException will be thrown from this function.

◆ DeviceProfileName

String^ IonicSecurity::SDK::CreateDeviceRequest::DeviceProfileName

The device profile name to be used for the device being created.

This (optional) name will be set as the name of the newly created device profile after successful registration.
